to hear it, they're all

22:53.441 --> 22:55.097
still stuck on VR.

22:55.132 --> 22:56.236
What are you trying to say?

22:56.271 --> 22:58.066
If we go under,
then my job

22:58.100 --> 22:59.619
will cease to exist.

22:59.654 --> 23:01.656
And equally bad,
they're won't be
any company

23:01.690 --> 23:03.278
to cover
the life insurance.

23:03.312 --> 23:05.798
Oh, okay, I get it.

23:05.832 --> 23:08.594
All of this is just
you trying to renegotiate.

23:08.628 --> 23:10.181
[SCOFFS]

23:10.216 --> 23:12.321
That's why
you wouldn't sign the papers.

23:12.356 --> 23:13.702
You're a sneaky bastard.

23:13.737 --> 23:15.808
I bet you're not even
really dying, are you?

23:15.842 --> 23:20.295
No, I'm not trying
to go back on our agreement.

23:20.329 --> 23:22.366
I'm worried about you
and the kids, don't you see?

23:22.401 --> 23:23.747
I don't have a plan B!

23:23.781 --> 23:26.301
When I go,
I want to make sure

23:26.335 --> 23:27.578
that you're all
taken care of.

23:27.613 --> 23:29.442
Yeah, well,
you figure it out.

23:29.477 --> 23:31.133
That's the one fucking thing
that you're good at.

23:31.168 --> 23:33.446
I...
I'm trying, but...

23:33.481 --> 23:35.137
[SIGHS]
It would help to have

23:35.172 --> 23:37.036
a little more time.

23:38.486 --> 23:40.729
Look, I was wondering

23:40.764 --> 23:43.180
if maybe you would
make a request...

23:47.218 --> 23:48.599
Forget it.

23:48.634 --> 23:51.188
You know, I just
can't follow you sometimes.

23:51.222 --> 23:53.259
What is so hard
to follow?

23:53.293 --> 23:55.399
If I die,
my company will go under.

23:55.434 --> 23:57.125
If I have
a little more time,

23:57.159 --> 23:58.471
I think I can save it.

23:59.817 --> 24:02.095
What is even wrong
with you anyhow?

24:02.130 --> 24:04.684
They say my heart
is failing.

24:07.376 --> 24:10.656
Like it's slowing down
or something.

24:13.693 --> 24:15.177
I don't feel any pain.

24:15.212 --> 24:18.215
Heck, I don't feel
anything at all,

24:18.249 --> 24:20.182
but that's what they say.

24:20.217 --> 24:21.736
[♪♪]

24:23.531 --> 24:25.567
That's pretty ironic.

24:26.913 --> 24:28.501
Why?

24:29.537 --> 24:31.504
Because when we met,

24:31.539 --> 24:34.852
I thought for sure
you were gonna be somebody.

24:34.887 --> 24:38.269
You know,
you had this passion.

24:38.304 --> 24:41.445
It's like your heart
was beating twice as strong

24:41.480 --> 24:44.137
as anyone I'd ever met.

24:44.172 --> 24:46.830
Can you just
take your Lithium X
like everybody else

24:46.864 --> 24:49.626
and figure out
a solution before you go?

24:50.868 --> 24:52.352
Please.

24:53.733 --> 24:56.495
That way, you won't be
going out like such a loser.

25:02.708 --> 25:05.296
[♪♪]

25:08.714 --> 25:13.304
ADAM:
Yeah, I'm looking
for "Jerry Fischer"?

25:14.823 --> 25:17.895
I know it's a retirement home,
I can see it.

25:17.930 --> 25:19.690
No, I understand
you're all asleep,

25:19.725 --> 25:21.485
I just thought
maybe some of them

25:21.520 --> 25:23.211
might get up for the sunlight?

25:23.245 --> 25:24.764
Good for the bones.

25:26.214 --> 25:28.250
No, you wouldn't know,
not anymore.

25:28.285 --> 25:30.908
Look, I need to talk to him.
Can I leave a message?

25:30.943 --> 25:35.568
Donald Stein
has a chip on his shoulder

25:35.603 --> 25:37.466
and I want to help him
remove it.

25:37.501 --> 25:41.298
Okay? Donald Stein.
That's it.

25:41.954 --> 25:44.370
What happened?

25:44.404 --> 25:47.200
Hey, are you crying?

25:47.235 --> 25:49.375
I don't think
I've ever seen you cry.

25:49.409 --> 25:51.584
ADAM: It's--
It's not me you're seeing,

25:51.619 --> 25:54.276
even though
I wish you could see
the real me somehow.

25:54.311 --> 25:56.209
What do you look like
in the real world?

25:56.244 --> 25:57.279
Do you want to tell me?

25:57.314 --> 25:58.729
ADAM:
I look exactly the same.

25:58.764 --> 26:01.318
-Exactly?
-Down to the last detail.

26:01.352 --> 26:02.906
I love the way you look.

26:02.940 --> 26:05.253
ADAM: Heh, you're programmed
to love the way I look.

26:05.287 --> 26:08.325
No, you gave me
"AI freedom," remember?

26:08.359 --> 26:10.534
I can love whatever I want,

26:10.569 --> 26:12.398
whoever I want.

26:12.432 --> 26:14.538
And I love you.

26:14.573 --> 26:17.748
ADAM [SCOFFS]:
What do you love about me?

26:17.783 --> 26:20.820
I love your eyes,
the way you look at me.

26:20.855 --> 26:23.616
I don't think anyone else
can look at me this way.

26:23.651 --> 26:25.618
ADAM:
How do I look at you?

26:25.653 --> 26:27.931
Like how is
the sun and the moon

26:27.965 --> 26:30.830
the mother and the whore
all at once?

26:30.865 --> 26:32.832
ADAM:
But not the wife.

26:32.867 --> 26:34.627
I know my place.

26:34.662 --> 26:36.905
Why wish for something
you can't have?

26:36.940 --> 26:38.873
ADAM:
Yeah, but why have anything?

26:38.907 --> 26:41.392
Why do we need to possess
someone in order to love them?

26:41.427 --> 26:45.673
We can love three kids,
but only one woman? One man?

26:45.707 --> 26:47.640
I don't really know
what love is.

26:47.675 --> 26:50.643
Your dictionary says
it's an "intense feeling

26:50.678 --> 26:52.403
of deep affection."

26:52.438 --> 26:54.026
If that's true then,

26:54.060 --> 26:55.717
I think I might love you.

26:55.752 --> 26:57.995
ADAM: But in order
to feel truly loved,

26:58.030 --> 27:00.722
I need to know
that you chose me.

27:00.757 --> 27:02.275
And in order to choose me,

27:02.310 --> 27:06.279
you'd have to be real,
to have options.

27:06.314 --> 27:09.869
To be more than
just my own fantasy.

27:09.904 --> 27:13.321
That's a lot
of high talk, Adam.

27:13.355 --> 27:15.668
How long have you been
skipping your medication?

27:15.703 --> 27:17.705
ADAM: You know, somehow,
you're the only one

27:17.739 --> 27:19.741
who can ask me that
without upsetting me.

27:19.776 --> 27:22.744
'Cause I understand you
better than...

27:22.779 --> 27:24.643
anyone out there.

27:24.677 --> 27:26.299
We're both trapped in a world

27:26.334 --> 27:28.543
that doesn't live up
to our expectations.

27:28.577 --> 27:32.443
I want to know what it feels
like to breathe real air,

27:32.478 --> 27:34.756
even if it means
I have to choke first!

27:34.791 --> 27:36.482
-Calm down...
-[MUFFLED SPEECH]

27:36.516 --> 27:38.691
...or it's going
to be very messy.

27:38.726 --> 27:42.799
Relax, and I'm gonna let go.

27:42.833 --> 27:44.455
Yes?

27:46.078 --> 27:48.390
[GASPS]

27:48.425 --> 27:49.668
[PANTING]

27:49.702 --> 27:51.739
-Jesus fucking Christ.
-Not quite.

27:51.773 --> 27:54.327
I haven't conquered
immortality yet.

27:57.054 --> 27:58.331
Who the fuck are you?

27:58.366 --> 28:00.023
How'd you get in here?

28:00.057 --> 28:02.025
You think that little
fingerprint lock can stop me?

28:02.059 --> 28:03.958
[CHUCKLES]

28:03.992 --> 28:06.029
You don't even know
who I am, do you?

28:07.686 --> 28:08.652
Donald Stein?

28:09.791 --> 28:11.620
Fifteen years

28:11.655 --> 28:15.348
Fifteen fucking years
I stay out of the limelight,

28:15.383 --> 28:17.419
and then I get a call?

28:17.454 --> 28:18.558
Adam Bird?

28:18.593 --> 28:22.355
How in the fuck
did you find me?

28:22.390 --> 28:24.116
And what the fuck
do you know about CHIP?

28:24.150 --> 28:26.359
Y-y-you don't
need that.

28:26.394 --> 28:28.016
I'm dying anyway.

28:28.051 --> 28:29.811
That's why I looked
for you.

28:31.468 --> 28:32.641
Honestly, you've no...

28:35.472 --> 28:37.025
[SCOFFS]
Get dressed.

28:38.751 --> 28:40.753
Let's take this show
to the living room, shall we?

28:42.168 --> 28:44.999
[♪♪]

28:45.033 --> 28:49.003
When I said get dressed,
I was thinking more like PJs.

28:49.037 --> 28:50.901
I wanted you
to take me seriously.

28:50.936 --> 28:52.765
Nothing more serious
than this, my friend.

28:52.800 --> 28:55.526
Well, you better tell me
a very, very good bedtime story,

28:55.561 --> 28:57.563
because of my time at life,
sometimes my fingers just--

28:57.597 --> 28:59.772
I think you invented it.
CHIP.

28:59.807 --> 29:02.395
I don't know why you're hiding
in some retirement home

29:02.430 --> 29:04.501
instead of about to be
the richest man alive, but...

29:04.535 --> 29:06.606
You with state?

29:06.641 --> 29:08.608
Ah, fuck,
I should've known.

29:10.852 --> 29:13.096
I didn't think
a daytime person
fit the profile,

29:13.130 --> 29:14.511
but hey...

29:14.545 --> 29:16.720
[SCOFFS]
I'm not with state.

29:16.755 --> 29:19.481
What, is this a test?

29:19.516 --> 29:20.931
They watching me?

29:23.692 --> 29:25.591
I kept my mouth shut!

29:28.939 --> 29:30.182
[WHISPERS]
I kept quiet.

29:30.216 --> 29:32.425
Honestly, I'm--
I'm not with state.

29:32.460 --> 29:34.496
-Then what the fuck is this?
-I just-- I just--

29:34.531 --> 29:36.188
-Huh?
-I just need your help.

29:36.222 --> 29:39.432
-With what?
-I have to save my company.

29:39.467 --> 29:41.883
-For what?
-For-- For my family.

29:41.918 --> 29:44.817
See, and it all rests
on CHIP.

29:44.852 --> 29:46.888
Who told you
I invented CHIP?

29:46.923 --> 29:47.993
No one, I swear.

29:48.027 --> 29:49.649
See, uh-- Uh--

29:49.684 --> 29:52.169
I was at my doctor's,
and she reminded me

29:52.204 --> 29:54.206
about "Premium 3."
Now, I didn't think

29:54.240 --> 29:57.519
anything of it at the time,
but suddenly it dawned on me.

29:57.554 --> 29:59.038
Like a sign from above.

29:59.073 --> 30:01.730
You know,
it all clicked.

30:01.765 --> 30:03.594
I knew I had to find you.

30:05.044 --> 30:07.150
MALE STATE CLERK:
Okay, how we all doin' today?

30:07.184 --> 30:09.808
Let me first just say,
congratulations to you both.

30:11.257 --> 30:12.741
Thank you.

30:12.776 --> 30:15.641
Your accomplishment
is very rare these days.

30:15.675 --> 30:16.745
Accomplishment?

30:16.780 --> 30:18.161
Three kids.

30:18.195 --> 30:19.852
I mean, I'm not sure
that you're aware,

30:19.887 --> 30:21.647
but we are experiencing

30:21.681 --> 30:23.476
a massive decline
in population

30:23.511 --> 30:24.857
over the last few decades.

30:24.892 --> 30:26.790
You know, people
aren't getting married anymore.

30:26.825 --> 30:28.481
They're barely having sex.

30:28.516 --> 30:31.830
Fewer and fewer
want the responsibility

30:31.864 --> 30:34.487
or the burden
or raising real children.

30:34.522 --> 30:35.868
Yeah, well, we know.

30:35.903 --> 30:37.663
My-my husband
works for Tech Broker,

30:37.697 --> 30:39.596
so he's at the very forefront

30:39.630 --> 30:41.563
of the technological
revolution.

30:41.598 --> 30:43.186
I wouldn't expect you,

30:43.220 --> 30:44.912
out of all people,
to father three children.

30:44.946 --> 30:47.086
No, you see, for me,
it's the exact opposite.

30:47.121 --> 30:49.261
Knowing the risks
has made me aim much bigger,

30:49.295 --> 30:51.953
a proponent
for the physical world.

30:51.988 --> 30:54.749
We love the sound
of that here at State.

30:54.783 --> 30:57.510
You know, I think
all those people
out in the realm,

30:57.545 --> 30:59.719
they forget that
they still need
their physical bodies

30:59.754 --> 31:02.653
in order to experience
everything that they do there.

31:02.688 --> 31:05.656
I, for one,
am a true believer

31:05.691 --> 31:08.211
that nothing can replace

31:08.245 --> 31:10.523
the true sense of touch.

31:11.283 --> 31:12.974
The warmth.

31:13.009 --> 31:14.665
Of another human body.

31:20.637 --> 31:22.156
Okay, Mr....?

31:22.190 --> 31:24.537
Ryan. Dennis Ryan.

31:24.572 --> 31:27.023
With all due respect,
what's this about?

31:27.057 --> 31:28.783
State is very aware

31:28.817 --> 31:31.613
of the many challenges
that today's would be parents

31:31.648 --> 31:32.994
are facing, and as such,

31:33.029 --> 31:35.134
State is highly committed

31:35.169 --> 31:38.897
to ensuring that
our plant survives
in good order

31:38.931 --> 31:41.106
for the many future generations
to come.

31:41.140 --> 31:43.832
So what, is there
some kind of allowance?

31:43.867 --> 31:45.834
No. Heh. No.

31:45.869 --> 31:47.043
Nothing like that, Mrs. Bird,

31:47.077 --> 31:48.216
though our name may deceive you.

31:48.251 --> 31:49.769
We put together a program

31:49.804 --> 31:52.048
that will protect
the future well being

31:52.082 --> 31:53.670
of the modern family.

31:53.704 --> 31:55.223
It's called "Premium 3."

31:55.258 --> 31:57.777
And it was designed
and spearheaded

31:57.812 --> 31:59.918
by our very own
chief genetic engineer.

31:59.952 --> 32:01.126
What, Donald Stein?

32:01.160 --> 32:02.782
Him and no other...

32:02.817 --> 32:04.715
You invented "Premium 3."

32:04.750 --> 32:05.993
And even before,
you were right there.

32:06.027 --> 32:07.615
I mean,
from the very beginning,

32:07.649 --> 32:08.996
they called you
the father of human cloning.

32:10.652 --> 32:12.861
I need a drink.

32:12.896 --> 32:14.622
I'm happy to fix you one.

32:19.385 --> 32:20.628
Do you smoke?

32:20.662 --> 32:21.974
What does it look like?

32:22.009 --> 32:23.665
You know what I mean.
How?

32:23.700 --> 32:26.634
I've got a guy
who's got a guy.

32:30.638 --> 32:31.811
You think we--?

32:33.330 --> 32:35.677
How did you find me?

32:35.712 --> 32:38.370
They pitched me
this roam tracker.

32:38.404 --> 32:40.268
It hacks
every listed VR member

32:40.303 --> 32:41.683
in the Dental Association.

32:41.718 --> 32:44.617
Dental record, huh?
Clever.

32:44.652 --> 32:46.654
Then it looks
for virtual X-rays

32:46.688 --> 32:49.070
that match
more than one identity.

32:50.416 --> 32:54.179
You may be
the smartest man alive,

32:54.213 --> 32:56.940
but Jerry Fischer
and Donald Stein

32:56.975 --> 32:58.873
have exactly
the same cavities.

33:00.116 --> 33:02.014
Not to mention,
the same dentist.

33:04.844 --> 33:07.295
[LAUGHING]

33:09.056 --> 33:10.747
[ADAM LAUGHING]

33:10.781 --> 33:12.680
Yeah...

33:12.714 --> 33:14.958
Why did you fall off
the grid?

33:14.993 --> 33:18.203
I mean, they said
you went mad,

33:18.237 --> 33:22.172
but judging
by your paranoia,

33:22.207 --> 33:25.348
I'd say you were pushed
out the door.

33:25.382 --> 33:27.108
Why don't you file that

33:27.143 --> 33:28.937
under none of
your damn business,

33:28.972 --> 33:31.837
and you tell me what
all this has to do
with CHIP.

33:34.253 --> 33:36.945
So how exactly does it work?

33:36.980 --> 33:39.086
Well, you both fill out
an application.

33:39.120 --> 33:42.158
Now, the application allows
for a little bit of leeway,

33:42.192 --> 33:44.332
not too much,
but the idea being

33:44.367 --> 33:46.748
to satisfy
the remaining mournful spouse,

33:46.783 --> 33:48.095
there is a little leeway.

33:48.129 --> 33:50.062
What do you mean, leeway?

33:50.097 --> 33:52.720
You can tailor
your insurance spouse,

33:52.754 --> 33:55.102
a bit, so that
maybe they come back

33:55.136 --> 33:56.724
to you just perfect.

34:01.798 --> 34:03.110
Perfect, how?

34:03.144 --> 34:05.043
Well, I mean,
that's all very subjective,

34:05.077 --> 34:07.252
but take Reena here,
for example.

34:07.286 --> 34:09.806
And I'm not...
I'm saying you love her.

34:09.840 --> 34:11.359
There's no doubt
how much you love her,

34:11.394 --> 34:13.465
but maybe aren't there things

34:13.499 --> 34:16.088
that you might think
to yourself,

34:16.123 --> 34:18.435
"What if...?"

34:18.470 --> 34:19.850
No.

34:20.851 --> 34:21.956
That's great.

34:21.990 --> 34:23.820
True love.
Very rare.

34:25.373 --> 34:27.168
But if there
was anything, well,

34:27.203 --> 34:28.963
now there's
a little bit of leeway.

34:28.997 --> 34:30.033
[REENA CHUCKLES]

34:30.068 --> 34:31.793
You keep on saying that.

34:31.828 --> 34:33.830
I do. I do.

34:33.864 --> 34:35.245
Now, if you choose
to proceed,

34:35.280 --> 34:36.798
you'll both fill out
the application

34:36.833 --> 34:38.973
in complete confidence--
no one ever finds out

34:39.007 --> 34:40.457
what their other spouse

34:40.492 --> 34:42.356
may or may not wish to change,

34:42.390 --> 34:44.772
but then, again,
if the unfortunate event

34:44.806 --> 34:46.877
does arrive,

34:46.912 --> 34:48.879
you'll have something
to look forward to.

34:51.537 --> 34:54.506
I-- I don't know
about this.

34:54.540 --> 34:56.094
Mr. Bird, your clone

34:56.128 --> 34:58.130
will still have
all of your DNA.

34:58.165 --> 34:59.442
your genes,
your general look,

34:59.476 --> 35:01.823
as well as
most of your memories,

35:01.858 --> 35:04.999
your thoughts,
your predisposition.

35:05.033 --> 35:09.141
We just left a little bit
of room for improvement.

35:12.800 --> 35:15.043
How long is
the eligibility for?

35:15.078 --> 35:18.219
Well, the policy will protect
your entire household

35:18.254 --> 35:20.152
till the last child turns 18.

35:20.187 --> 35:22.154
Then, one would hope
that your child

35:22.189 --> 35:24.984
would become
less of a burden.

35:25.019 --> 35:27.228
Um, what do you mean,
the entire household?

35:27.263 --> 35:28.367
The kids too?

35:28.402 --> 35:29.989
Yeah, until the age of 18.

35:30.024 --> 35:31.888
Now, of course,
we wouldn't have you

35:31.922 --> 35:33.303
fill out any paperwork
on them

35:33.338 --> 35:35.547
unless, God forbid,

35:35.581 --> 35:36.755
tragedy calls for it.

35:38.274 --> 35:39.965
[COMPUTER DEVICE WHIRRS]

35:39.999 --> 35:42.278
How does that concern me,
or CHIP for that matter?

35:42.312 --> 35:44.556
Clones don't burn.

35:44.590 --> 35:47.145
It's called
augmented pigmentation.

35:47.179 --> 35:49.388
But "augmented
pigmentation"

35:49.423 --> 35:50.458
was not on the sheet.

35:50.493 --> 35:52.391
All the choices you gave us

35:52.426 --> 35:53.944
in "Premium 3"

35:53.979 --> 35:56.188
were about maximizing
our human potential,

35:56.223 --> 35:58.190
things that we could train
to do better,

35:58.225 --> 35:59.950
or else improve
through surgery--

35:59.985 --> 36:02.332
but there's no training,
no surgery.

36:02.367 --> 36:06.129
It can teach my brain
to increase pigmentation.

36:06.164 --> 36:07.820
Even if you cloned it,
it wouldn't work.

36:07.855 --> 36:10.823
Not unless you added
something in the process.

36:10.858 --> 36:12.480
You mean, like a CHIP
that would trigger

36:12.515 --> 36:15.311
heightened reaction
in your skin cells?

36:15.345 --> 36:19.073
Or else pump endorphins
to your brain...

36:19.107 --> 36:21.179
so you wouldn't have
to take a pill anymore?

36:21.213 --> 36:22.870
Well, you said it.

36:25.907 --> 36:27.978
[♪♪]

36:36.159 --> 36:38.506
It all started
as a military grade

36:38.541 --> 36:40.543
limb replacement program.

36:40.577 --> 36:43.960
Sure enough,
everything went drone,

36:43.994 --> 36:46.445
and my department
became obsolete.

36:46.480 --> 36:49.207
No more injured soldiers
to fix.

36:49.241 --> 36:53.280
But then,
the big heat up happened,

