1:27:35.491 --> 1:27:39.426
Well, that's, that's
a very long story.

1:27:40.979 --> 1:27:42.153
I have time.

1:27:43.361 --> 1:27:46.157
Okay. Well, first,

1:27:46.191 --> 1:27:48.539
my wife caught me
having a virtual affair.

1:27:48.573 --> 1:27:50.334
Then she wanted me replaced,

1:27:50.368 --> 1:27:53.026
but when I wanted
to stick around a little longer,

1:27:53.060 --> 1:27:55.235
she ordered
my virtual assassination.

1:27:55.270 --> 1:27:58.134
She killed me off on the realm!
And-and left me this house!

1:27:58.169 --> 1:28:00.551
I guess she forgot that
you would be coming here first

1:28:00.585 --> 1:28:02.415
and she certainly
did not expect

1:28:02.449 --> 1:28:04.589
to get hit by a car.

1:28:04.624 --> 1:28:08.593
And all of this, all of this,
this fucking warped reality

1:28:08.628 --> 1:28:10.940
is because of
that Donald fucking Stein.

1:28:10.975 --> 1:28:12.356
Heh, can you believe that?

1:28:12.390 --> 1:28:15.048
How one person
can set something in motion

1:28:15.082 --> 1:28:18.327
and the rest of the world
is never the same again!

1:28:18.362 --> 1:28:19.639
[DRY CHUCKLE]

1:28:19.673 --> 1:28:21.606
I feel like
getting in my car,

1:28:21.641 --> 1:28:23.712
and going down
to that retirement home

1:28:23.746 --> 1:28:27.336
and finding
that motherfucker who,

1:28:27.371 --> 1:28:29.476
who defiled my fantasy,

1:28:29.511 --> 1:28:34.067
who-who made it possible
for my wife to make
a better version of me.

1:28:34.101 --> 1:28:36.518
I feel like going down there
and ending him!

1:28:36.552 --> 1:28:39.037
What do you think
about that?!

1:28:40.211 --> 1:28:41.454
I think it reminds me

1:28:41.488 --> 1:28:44.319
of our favorite
high school play.

1:28:44.353 --> 1:28:46.286
What?

1:28:46.321 --> 1:28:47.287
What play?

1:28:47.322 --> 1:28:49.082
You don't remember?

1:28:50.152 --> 1:28:51.671
You must remember!

1:28:51.705 --> 1:28:53.258
We were promising.

1:28:53.293 --> 1:28:55.157
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

1:28:55.191 --> 1:28:56.192
Sure you do.

1:28:57.159 --> 1:28:58.505
Repeat after me.

1:28:58.540 --> 1:29:00.404
I promise, it'll
all come back to you.

1:29:02.578 --> 1:29:05.719
To be, or not to be.

1:29:05.754 --> 1:29:08.239
That is the question.

1:29:08.273 --> 1:29:10.379
Whether it is nobler
in the mind...

1:29:10.414 --> 1:29:13.106
[BOTH RECITING]
to suffer the slings and arrows

1:29:13.140 --> 1:29:15.246
of outrageous fortune.

1:29:18.214 --> 1:29:20.700
But to take arms
against the sea
of troubles.

1:29:20.734 --> 1:29:22.357
Yes, you remember!

1:29:22.391 --> 1:29:26.015
And by opposing,
end them.

1:29:26.050 --> 1:29:27.292
Go on!

1:29:27.327 --> 1:29:31.331
To die, to sleep.

1:29:31.366 --> 1:29:33.575
To sleep,
perchance to dream!

1:29:33.609 --> 1:29:35.059
I, there is the rub.

1:29:35.093 --> 1:29:36.301
For in that sleep
of death,

1:29:36.336 --> 1:29:37.648
what dreams may come.

1:29:37.682 --> 1:29:40.133
When we have shuffled off
this mortal coil...

1:29:40.167 --> 1:29:41.617
Must give us pause.

1:29:41.652 --> 1:29:43.792
There's a respect
that makes calamity

1:29:43.826 --> 1:29:45.207
of so long life.

1:29:45.241 --> 1:29:46.484
For who would bear

1:29:46.519 --> 1:29:49.176
the whips and scorns
of time.

1:29:49.211 --> 1:29:51.420
The oppressor's wrong,
the proud man's contumely...

1:29:51.455 --> 1:29:53.560
The pangs
of despised love,

1:29:53.595 --> 1:29:56.080
the law's delay,
the insolence of office...

1:29:56.114 --> 1:29:59.117
The spurns that patient merit
of the unworthy takes...

1:29:59.152 --> 1:30:03.294
When he himself
might his quietus make,

1:30:03.328 --> 1:30:06.159
with a bare bodkin?

1:30:06.193 --> 1:30:07.436
Who would fardels bare,

1:30:07.471 --> 1:30:10.232
to grunt and sweat
under a weary life...

1:30:10.266 --> 1:30:12.130
But that the dread
of something after death...

1:30:12.165 --> 1:30:13.442
The undiscovered country!

1:30:13.477 --> 1:30:15.133
For whose bourn
no traveler returns...

1:30:15.168 --> 1:30:16.169
Puzzles the will!

1:30:16.203 --> 1:30:17.377
And makes us rather bare,

1:30:17.412 --> 1:30:18.447
those ills we have...

1:30:18.482 --> 1:30:20.138
BOTH:
Than fly to others

1:30:20.173 --> 1:30:21.795
that we know not of...

1:30:24.108 --> 1:30:29.147
Thus conscience does
make cowards of us all,

1:30:29.182 --> 1:30:32.772
And thus the native hue
of resolution

1:30:32.806 --> 1:30:36.810
Is sicklied o'er with
the pale cast of thought,

1:30:36.845 --> 1:30:41.297
And enterprises
of great pitch and moment

1:30:41.332 --> 1:30:44.231
With this regard
their currents turn awry

1:30:44.266 --> 1:30:46.579
And lose the name of action.

1:30:50.203 --> 1:30:53.171
Soft you now,

1:30:53.206 --> 1:30:56.243
the fair...

1:30:56.278 --> 1:30:57.486
Maria...

1:30:59.523 --> 1:31:02.595
Nymph, in thy orisons,

1:31:02.629 --> 1:31:05.460
be all my sins
remembered...

1:31:08.393 --> 1:31:10.430
That's beautiful work,
Adam.

1:31:10.465 --> 1:31:12.156
Great work!

1:31:13.260 --> 1:31:15.262
[SOUND OF APPLAUSE]

1:31:15.297 --> 1:31:17.299
ADAM REPLICA: Adam Bird,
ladies and gentlemen.

1:31:17.333 --> 1:31:19.474
To Adam Bird.

1:31:27.205 --> 1:31:29.518
I'm not Adam Bird.

1:31:29.553 --> 1:31:31.796
You're Adam Bird now.
I'm...

1:31:31.831 --> 1:31:33.488
Richard Burbage.

1:31:33.522 --> 1:31:34.799
What did she call you?

1:31:34.834 --> 1:31:36.249
Richard Burbage.

1:31:36.283 --> 1:31:39.597
[LAUGHS]
That's hysterical.

1:31:39.632 --> 1:31:40.736
Why?

1:31:40.771 --> 1:31:42.566
-Look it up.
-No.

1:31:42.600 --> 1:31:44.913
Because I'd have log in
as Richard Burbage

1:31:44.947 --> 1:31:46.431
to look up
Richard Burbage,

1:31:46.466 --> 1:31:49.262
and I won't do it
because that's not who I am!

1:31:49.296 --> 1:31:50.746
Or is it?

1:31:50.781 --> 1:31:52.541
Maybe that is me.
Maybe I'm just a guy

1:31:52.576 --> 1:31:54.370
who secretly wishes
he was Adam Bird.

1:31:54.405 --> 1:31:55.820
But that's you.

1:31:55.855 --> 1:31:58.374
You are everything that
I would ever wish to be.

1:31:58.409 --> 1:31:59.790
And Reena somehow
figured that out,

1:31:59.824 --> 1:32:02.517
and she, she knew
what I wanted to be

1:32:02.551 --> 1:32:03.863
better than I did...

1:32:03.897 --> 1:32:05.381
There's no shame
in admitting

1:32:05.416 --> 1:32:06.555
that Reena's version
of Adam Bird

1:32:06.590 --> 1:32:07.660
is a much better one.

1:32:07.694 --> 1:32:09.696
It's holistic,
and less egotistical.

1:32:09.731 --> 1:32:13.148
It's a version much more geared
to please other people.

1:32:14.874 --> 1:32:18.187
Why don't you just embrace
your new identity, Richard?

1:32:19.810 --> 1:32:21.950
I-I don't know...

1:32:21.984 --> 1:32:23.952
I don't think
I can carry on,

1:32:23.986 --> 1:32:26.368
knowing there's a replica
of me out there.

1:32:26.402 --> 1:32:28.404
It just,
it doesn't seem right.

1:32:29.647 --> 1:32:32.374
There should be
only one Adam Bird.

1:32:36.861 --> 1:32:38.518
But you said it
yourself, Richard.

1:32:38.553 --> 1:32:40.693
You're no longer
Adam Bird.

1:32:40.727 --> 1:32:42.867
You're Richard Burbage.

1:32:42.902 --> 1:32:44.455
I don't know
who I am anymore.

1:32:44.489 --> 1:32:45.698
I don't even know
what I am!

1:32:47.734 --> 1:32:50.461
I was told I can fit
inside a CHIP.

1:32:51.773 --> 1:32:54.292
Everything I am
and ever was

1:32:54.327 --> 1:32:58.365
can fit inside
one tiny microchip.

1:32:59.850 --> 1:33:02.611
And there'll still be plenty
of room left for more.

1:33:03.854 --> 1:33:04.993
What does it all mean?

1:33:05.027 --> 1:33:08.306
It means you can live on
for eternity.

1:33:14.692 --> 1:33:18.593
This whole flesh and blood
business-- it's near done.

1:33:21.768 --> 1:33:23.839
Even us clones,

1:33:23.874 --> 1:33:28.464
we're just like BluRays
to your VHS tapes...

1:33:28.499 --> 1:33:31.502
Some transitional upgrade
that will doubtless

1:33:31.536 --> 1:33:33.642
be obsolete
in due time.

1:33:33.677 --> 1:33:37.646
In the end,
we're all gonna go virtual

1:33:37.681 --> 1:33:41.270
and exist
in some cloud of neurons.

1:33:41.305 --> 1:33:42.617
[GASPS]

1:33:43.790 --> 1:33:45.654
Only the sand
will be left here.

1:33:45.689 --> 1:33:50.348
Sand and silicon...

1:33:50.383 --> 1:33:54.525
All the rest will be
out there on the realm,

1:33:54.559 --> 1:34:00.807
and each of us will be
their own special virtual god.

1:34:02.395 --> 1:34:04.846
But I was
virtually assassinated.

1:34:06.019 --> 1:34:07.952
I can only exist virtually

1:34:07.987 --> 1:34:09.989
as Richard Burbage.

1:34:12.577 --> 1:34:14.752
That is
if I let you live...

1:34:16.064 --> 1:34:17.652
I bet I can
find a way to reverse this

1:34:17.686 --> 1:34:19.446
if I stick around
a little longer.

1:34:19.481 --> 1:34:20.965
Wait, wait, wait...

1:34:21.000 --> 1:34:23.830
Why did your wife order
a virtual assassination?

1:34:23.865 --> 1:34:24.831
You never told me.

1:34:30.009 --> 1:34:31.286
I'm dying.

1:34:37.533 --> 1:34:39.328
My heart,
it's just not as certain

1:34:39.363 --> 1:34:41.814
it wants to keep beating
any longer.

1:34:45.852 --> 1:34:48.096
I need a new heart.

1:34:48.130 --> 1:34:49.718
Do you know what I think?

1:34:49.753 --> 1:34:51.099
I think
you've been skipping

1:34:51.133 --> 1:34:54.378
your medication
for months now.

1:34:57.105 --> 1:35:00.487
You owe back
on all these pills...

1:35:02.455 --> 1:35:03.801
You should take 'em.

1:35:05.009 --> 1:35:08.461
You should
take these pills

1:35:08.495 --> 1:35:11.844
and balance yourself out
so you can think straight

1:35:11.878 --> 1:35:14.570
and find
the right solution here.

1:35:14.605 --> 1:35:15.951
Think about your kids...

1:35:17.090 --> 1:35:18.747
You have to be strong
for them.

1:35:20.715 --> 1:35:22.993
You have
to sacrifice yourself...

1:35:57.199 --> 1:35:58.407
No.

1:35:58.442 --> 1:35:59.995
You're just trying
to kill me.

1:36:00.030 --> 1:36:02.411
You're trying to kill me
and take my place.
Isn't that right?!

1:36:02.446 --> 1:36:04.413
"Too-cool-for-school" Adam,
"big-dick" Adam,

1:36:04.448 --> 1:36:06.036
coming here to steal
my wife and kids...

1:36:06.070 --> 1:36:07.623
Is that's what you think
is gonna happen?!

1:36:07.658 --> 1:36:09.418
Because I have
a different ending in mind.

1:36:09.453 --> 1:36:11.627
-[ADAM GRUNTS]
-I can't let you kill me.

1:36:11.662 --> 1:36:14.423
I'm programmed with
a self defense mechanism.

1:36:15.770 --> 1:36:17.081
We just call it survival!

1:36:34.823 --> 1:36:36.411
Fuck.

1:36:41.761 --> 1:36:44.074
[♪♪]

